---
import SiteLayout from '../../layouts/SiteLayout.astro';
import PrinterTable from '../../components/PrinterTable.astro';
---

<SiteLayout
  title="Best OpenPrinter Alternatives You Can Buy Now"
  description="Practical OpenPrinter alternatives for buyers who want no mandatory ink subscription, lower lock-in risk, refillable ink, or Linux-friendly printing today."
>
  <div class="article">
    <p class="eyebrow" style="color: var(--amber);">OpenPrinter alternatives</p>
    <h1>Waiting for OpenPrinter? Buy around the lock-in problem today.</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      The best alternative is not a single perfect printer. It depends on whether you care most about ink cost, Linux support, text printing, or avoiding subscriptions.
    </p>
  </div>

  <section class="section alt">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-head">
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow" style="color: var(--amber);">Shortlist</p>
          <h2>Current practical candidates</h2>
        </div>
        <p>
          This table is shared with the main buying guides, so the OpenPrinter traffic feeds the long-term printer database instead of becoming a dead-end topic.
        </p>
      </div>
      <PrinterTable />
    </div>
  </section>

  <article class="article">
    <section class="article-section">
      <h2>How to choose an alternative</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>For frequent color printing, start with refillable tank models and compare ink bottle pricing.</li>
        <li>For text-heavy work, a monochrome laser printer is often the lowest-friction no-subscription choice.</li>
        <li>For Linux, confirm CUPS, AirPrint, driverless printing, or vendor driver support before purchase.</li>
        <li>For third-party ink or toner, check current reports before accepting a firmware update.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>
  </article>
</SiteLayout>
